    "It focuses on understanding concepts, experiences, and phenomena from a subjective perspective, often exploring meanings, interpretations, and patterns rather than relying on quantifiable data (Merriam & Tisdell, 2015; Sandelowski, 2010).",
    "This type of research involves using words and observations as data rather than numbers.",
    "It seeks to answer the \"why\" and \"how\" questions, that is, to gain insight into human behavior, attitudes, motivations, values, and culture to explain why users do what they do (Creswell & Poth, 2016).",
    "Therefore, we have adopted this methodology to address the research question in our study.",
    "Moreover, we used semi-structured interviews because they could shed light on pertinent real-world questions related to the study (Catterall, 2000; Maxwell, 2008)."
